{"word":"στρατηλατέω","slug":"στρατηλατέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στρατηλατέω</b></el> <el>(στρᾰτηλᾰτέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to lead an army into the field</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to be commander of, to command</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <el>στρᾰτηλάτης</el>\n"}]}